label.value: Treatment Based on Genomic Alteration

value.value: A question to determine if any therapeutic interventions, planned or performed, are tailored to an individual's specific genetic change or defect.

label.value: Is Patient Eligible for Systemic Therapy in Provider's Opinion

value.value: A question regarding the eligibility of a patient for systemic therapy, based on the medical provider's opinion.

label.value: Treatment Planned Prior to Return of Genomic Testing Not Already Recorded

value.value: A question to determine if there are plans for treatment prior to the results of genetic testing that have not yet been recorded.

label.value: Chromosome Fragile Site

value.value: Heritable sensitive regions of chromosomes which show up in vitro as non-staining bands. They are associated with chromosome breakage and other aberrations. No abnormal phenotype has been definitely identified with autosomal fragile sites, but some rare autosomal recessive disorders may be due to homozygosity for fragile sites. A fragile site on the X chromosome is associated with Fragile X Syndrome. Fragile sites are designated by the letters "fra" followed by the designation for the specific chromosome and locus.

label.value: Consortium for Molecular and Cellular Characterization of Screen-Detected Lesions

value.value: A consortium consisting of independent, multi-disciplinary teams that undertake comprehensive molecular and cellular characterizations of tumor tissue, cell, and microenvironment components to distinguish screen-detected early lesions from interval and symptom-detected cancers.

label.value: Porta Heptis

value.value: A transverse fissure on the visceral surface of the liver between the caudate and quadrate lobes, lodging the portal vein, hepatic artery, hepatic nerve plexus, hepatic ducts, and lymphatic vessels.

label.value: Hepatoduodenal Ligament

value.value: The portion of the lesser omentum between the liver and the duodenum, containing the hepatic artery, the common bile duct, the portal vein, lymphatic vessels, and the hepatic plexus of nerves.

label.value: Mesenteric Root

value.value: The origin of the mesentery arising from the parietal peritoneum.

label.value: Renal Pedicle

value.value: The recessed central fissure of the kidney, though which pass the ureter and vessels of the kidney.

label.value: Sciatic Notch

value.value: Either of the two notches on the dorsal border of each side of the pelvis that when closed off by the sacrospinous and sacrotuberous ligaments form the corresponding sciatic foramina.

label.value: Neural Foramen

value.value: Any of the openings between the vertebrae, through which pass the spinal nerve roots.

label.value: Iliac Vessel

value.value: Any of the branches of the vessels arising from the common iliac artery or vein, located in the pelvis.

label.value: Clavien-Dindo Classification of Surgical Complications

value.value: A classification system for post-surgical complications based on the type of therapy needed to correct the complication, consisting of a 5-grade rating scale.

label.value: Free Radioiodine

value.value: Radioactive iodine that is not attached to another molecule.

label.value: Cell Surface Structure
Five Hundred

value.value: The natural number greater than 499 and less than 501 and the quantity that it denotes.

label.value: Lower Gastrointestinal Tract Cancer TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of lower gastrointestinal tract cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Anal Cancer TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of anal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. This staging system applies to all carcinomas arising in the anal canal, including carcinomas that arise within anorectal fistulas and those arising in the perianal area (anal margin). High-grade neuroendocrine carcinomas (small cell neuroendocrine carcinoma and large cell neuroendocrine carcinoma) are staged using this system. There is no AJCC staging system for anal mucosal melanomas and anal well-differentiated neuroendocrine tumors. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of anal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Anal Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of anal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Anal Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of anal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Anal Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of anal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Anal Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Chromosome Structure

value.value: The 3-D organization of histones and other proteins on chromosomal DNA in the nucleus and allow for its form and function during cellular growth and division.

label.value: Anal Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of anal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Anal Cancer pTX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer pTis TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with a finding of high-grade squamous intraepithelial lesion (previously termed carcinoma in situ, Bowen disease, anal intraepithelial neoplasia II-III, high-grade anal intraepithelial neoplasia). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with tumor 2 cm or smaller. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with tumor larger than 2 cm but equal to or smaller than 5 cm. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with tumor larger than 5 cm. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anti-CD20 Monoclonal Antibody-FITC

value.value: An immunoconjugate composed of a monoclonal antibody directed against the human antigen CD20 that is conjugated to the fluorescein derivative and fluorochrome fluorescein isothiocyanate (FITC), with potential use for imaging and detection of CD20-expressing cells. Upon application of anti-CD20-FITC to a cell preparation, anti-CD20-FITC targets and binds to CD20-expressing cells. Then, CD20-expressing cells in the sample can be imaged using fluorescence-based imaging techniques or separated from other cells present in the preparation using fluorescence-activated cell sorting (FACS). CD20 is a non-glycosylated cell surface phosphoprotein that is exclusively expressed on B-cells during most stages of B-cell development; it is involved in the regulation of B-cell differentiation and is overexpressed on certain types of cancer cells.

label.value: Anal Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with tumor of any size invading adjacent organ(s), such as the vagina, urethra, or bladder. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of anal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Fundus

value.value: The bottom portion or the portion that is furthest from the opening of a hollow organ.

label.value: Anal Cancer pNX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with no metastasis to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with metastasis in inguinal, mesorectal, internal iliac, or external iliac nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer pN1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with metastasis in inguinal, mesorectal, or internal iliac lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer pN1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with metastasis in external iliac lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Anal Cancer pN1c TNM Finding v8

value.value: Anal cancer with metastasis in external iliac with any N1a nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Funded Institution

value.value: The institution where the funded principal investigator is on staff.

label.value: Anal Canal Cancer by AJCC v6 and v7 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of anal canal cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer, 6th and 7th editions. This staging system applies to carcinomas arising in the anal canal only; melanomas, carcinoid tumors, sarcomas, and perianal tumors are not included. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: TNFSF14 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in both T-cell proliferation and tumor cell apoptosis.

label.value: TNFSF14 wt Allele

value.value: Tumor necrosis factor ligand superfamily member 14 (240 aa, ~26 kDa) is encoded by the human TNFSF14 gene. This protein is involved in the regulation of both T-cell proliferation and apoptosis.

label.value: Protein Domain

value.value: A structurally or functionally defined protein region.

label.value: Tumor Necrosis Factor Ligand Superfamily Member 14

value.value: Tumor necrosis factor ligand superfamily member 14 (240 aa, ~26 kDa) is encoded by the human TNFSF14 gene. This protein is involved in the regulation of both T-cell proliferation and apoptosis.

label.value: TNFSF9 Gene

value.value: This gene plays a role in T-lymphocyte activation.
